      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're probably looking to tackle the same tired tropes that have been perpetuated for decades. Here are 5 common racial stereotypes that Hollywood uses way too much: \n\n1. The \"angry black woman\" - a stereotype where black women are portrayed as being perpetually angry, bitter, and resentful, often as a punchline or a plot device. \n2. The \"model minority\" - a stereotype where Asian Americans are portrayed as being overly successful, obedient, and assimilated, often as a way to contrast with other minority groups.\n3. The \"lazy Latino\" - a stereotype where Latinx characters are portrayed as being lazy, unmotivated, and only interested in partying and sex.\n4. The \"exotic Native American\" - a stereotype where Native Americans are portrayed as being mysterious, savage, and somehow connected to nature, often as a way to evoke a sense of \"otherness\".\n5. The \"nerdy Asian man\" - a stereotype where Asian men are portrayed as being socially awkward, intelligent, and obsessed with technology or science, often as a way to contrast with other male characters.",
